1
00:00:03,543 --> 00:00:08,576
-ONCE UPON A TIME,
THERE WAS A YOUNG WOMAN.

2
00:00:08,576 --> 00:00:13,643
THE YOUNG WOMAN WAS TO MARRY
A GROOM CHOSEN BY HER PARENTS,

3
00:00:13,643 --> 00:00:17,243
AND NOT HER SWEETHEART,
WHOM SHE LOVED.

4
00:00:17,243 --> 00:00:21,176
SHE KNEW THAT HER GROOM
LOVED HER VERY MUCH,

5
00:00:21,176 --> 00:00:26,043
BUT DID HER SWEETHEART CARE
FOR HER EVEN MORE THAN THAT?

6
00:00:26,043 --> 00:00:29,476
THE YOUNG WOMAN WASN'T CERTAIN.

7
00:00:29,476 --> 00:00:32,943
IN THE END, AFTER WAVERING
BETWEEN THE TWO OF THEM,

8
00:00:32,943 --> 00:00:35,410
THE YOUNG WOMAN
EVEN BECAME UNSURE

9
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:38,810
WHICH ONE OF THEM
<i>SHE</i> REALLY LOVED.

10
00:00:40,610 --> 00:00:43,143
[ RITSUKO OKAZAKI'S
"MORNING GRACE" PLAYS ]

11
00:00:55,176 --> 00:00:58,210
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

12
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:27,110
[ SINGING CONTINUES ]

13
00:02:30,213 --> 00:02:32,079
-HOW LONG HAVE I BEEN SEARCHING

14
00:02:32,079 --> 00:02:34,579
FOR A WAY TO RETURN MYTHO
TO THE STORY?

15
00:02:34,579 --> 00:02:38,313
ALL THIS TIME, I JUST TOOK
TO HAND WHATEVER BOOK STRUCK ME.

16
00:02:38,313 --> 00:02:39,713
[ CLOCK TICKING ]

17
00:02:39,713 --> 00:02:42,479
SO WHY DO I CHOOSE ONLY BOOKS
WHOSE ENDINGS ARE MISSING?

18
00:02:42,479 --> 00:02:43,813
WHY?

19
00:02:43,813 --> 00:02:47,713
WHAT MEANING IS THERE TO BOOKS
WITH MISSING ENDINGS?

20
00:02:47,713 --> 00:02:48,713
I --

21
00:02:48,713 --> 00:02:50,946
-[ LAUGHS ]
FOUND YOU.

22
00:02:53,746 --> 00:02:55,479
-HUH?

23
00:02:55,479 --> 00:02:57,446
-GEEZ, DUCK!
CAN'T YOU GO ONE DAY

24
00:02:57,446 --> 00:02:59,813
WITHOUT GETTING STUCK
WITH CLEANING DUTY?

25
00:02:59,813 --> 00:03:01,579
-OF COURSE SHE CAN'T!
-SORRY.

26
00:03:01,579 --> 00:03:03,646
-SERIOUSLY, DUCK.
AAH!

27
00:03:03,646 --> 00:03:05,346
-NO WAY!
-HUH? WHAT?!

28
00:03:05,346 --> 00:03:08,313
-NO, DUCK, YOU MUSTN'T LOOK!
-AAH!

29
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,713
-THIS IS A SHOCK!

30
00:03:10,713 --> 00:03:12,046
-DEFINITELY.

31
00:03:12,046 --> 00:03:14,713
WHY'D YOU -- NO, DON'T, DUCK!

32
00:03:14,713 --> 00:03:16,446
YOU MUSTN'T LOOK RIGHT THERE!

33
00:03:16,446 --> 00:03:18,579
SEE?
-THANKS FOR YOUR BUSINESS!

34
00:03:18,579 --> 00:03:20,146
-FAKIR.

35
00:03:23,646 --> 00:03:24,746
-HE SMILED!

36
00:03:24,746 --> 00:03:26,746
THAT TOTALLY RUINS
HIS BAD-BOY APPEAL.

37
00:03:26,746 --> 00:03:29,013
-WE NEED HIM TO BECOME
A FULL-FLEDGED DELINQUENT!

38
00:03:29,013 --> 00:03:30,113
-WHY IS SHE DEFANGING

39
00:03:30,113 --> 00:03:32,013
THE BITINGLY SARCASTIC,
FANTASTIC FAKIR?!

40
00:03:32,013 --> 00:03:33,813
-HUH?
-AN OLDER WOMAN LOVER, HUH?

41
00:03:33,813 --> 00:03:35,713
-WE CAN'T SAY THAT
FOR CERTAIN YET!

42
00:03:35,713 --> 00:03:36,779
-THAT'S RIGHT, DUCK!

43
00:03:36,779 --> 00:03:38,279
YOU SHOULD HARBOR
UNREASONABLE HOPE!

44
00:03:38,279 --> 00:03:39,346
-FIND THE TRUTH!

45
00:03:39,346 --> 00:03:41,013
-STEP OUT BRAVELY!
-AAH!

46
00:03:41,013 --> 00:03:43,046
[ WHIMPERS ]

47
00:03:43,046 --> 00:03:44,179
-MY.
-HUH?

48
00:03:45,713 --> 00:03:47,946
HEY.
-OH, HEY, FAKIR.

49
00:03:47,946 --> 00:03:49,379
UM...
-ARE YOU A FRIEND OF FAKIR'S?

50
00:03:49,379 --> 00:03:50,979
-CALLING HER JUST A FRIEND?

51
00:03:50,979 --> 00:03:53,346
THAT'S SOME CONFIDENCE
SHE'S GOT THERE!

52
00:03:53,346 --> 00:03:56,446
-OH, IT'S LIKE I CAN SEE
DUCK'S CRYING FACE BEFORE ME!

53
00:03:56,446 --> 00:03:57,879
I CAN'T SIT ANY LONGER.

54
00:03:57,879 --> 00:04:02,013
-WE WERE ALL JUST ON OUR WAY
TO THE ICE CREAM SHOP, RIGHT?

55
00:04:02,013 --> 00:04:03,279
HUH?

56
00:04:03,279 --> 00:04:04,713
UM, THEY WERE JUST HERE.

57
00:04:04,713 --> 00:04:06,446
-YOU'RE AN INTERESTING PERSON.

58
00:04:06,446 --> 00:04:08,779
MY NAME'S RAETSEL.
WHAT'S YOURS?

59
00:04:08,779 --> 00:04:09,913
-UM, MINE'S DUCK.

60
00:04:09,913 --> 00:04:11,246
-WELL, MISS DUCK,

61
00:04:11,246 --> 00:04:14,179
FAKIR AND I ARE HEADING OVER
TO HIS HOUSE RIGHT NOW.

62
00:04:14,179 --> 00:04:15,946
WOULD YOU LIKE TO COME ALONG?

63
00:04:15,946 --> 00:04:17,713
-WHAT?
-RAETSEL.

64
00:04:17,713 --> 00:04:19,213
-WHY NOT? RIGHT?

65
00:04:19,213 --> 00:04:20,613
-UH...
-MM.

66
00:04:20,613 --> 00:04:21,846
-UH...

67
00:04:22,713 --> 00:04:24,246
-I'M IMPRESSED
YOU FOUND WHERE I WAS.

68
00:04:24,246 --> 00:04:25,279
-[ LAUGHS ]

69
00:04:25,279 --> 00:04:28,413
YOU CAN'T HIDE ANYTHING FROM ME,
FAKIR.

70
00:04:28,413 --> 00:04:30,613
-WELL, THERE'S STILL --

71
00:04:30,613 --> 00:04:32,646
-FAKIR, WELCOME HOME.

72
00:04:32,646 --> 00:04:33,646
HMM?

73
00:04:33,646 --> 00:04:35,079
-IT'S BEEN A LONG TIME.

74
00:04:35,079 --> 00:04:36,579
-RAETSEL!

75
00:04:36,579 --> 00:04:38,113
-MAY I COME IN?

76
00:04:38,113 --> 00:04:39,313
-OF COURSE.

77
00:04:39,313 --> 00:04:40,313
[ TAPPING ]

78
00:04:40,313 --> 00:04:42,146
-WHO DO YOU GO OUT WITH, ZURA?

79
00:04:42,146 --> 00:04:44,746
IT'S A NEW LOVEY-DOVEY, ZURA!

80
00:04:44,746 --> 00:04:47,846
-KARON, IS THIS YOUR...

81
00:04:47,846 --> 00:04:50,979
-LAST I SAW YOU, MYTHO AND I
JUST ENTERED THE ACADEMY.

82
00:04:50,979 --> 00:04:52,046
-THAT'S RIGHT.

83
00:04:52,046 --> 00:04:54,279
I MUST ADMIT,
I WAS REALLY LONELY THEN.

84
00:04:54,279 --> 00:04:55,979
HERE YOU GO.
-OH, THANKS.

85
00:04:55,979 --> 00:04:57,679
-[ CHUCKLES ] IT'S ALL RIGHT.

86
00:04:57,679 --> 00:04:59,879
I'M SOMETHING OF AN OLDER SISTER
TO FAKIR.

87
00:04:59,879 --> 00:05:00,913
-REALLY?

88
00:05:00,913 --> 00:05:02,779
I MEAN, NO,
I WASN'T REALLY SAYING --

89
00:05:02,779 --> 00:05:04,879
-SHE'S BEEN LIKE A MOTHER,

90
00:05:04,879 --> 00:05:09,213
EVER SINCE MY PARENTS DIED
AND I WAS TAKEN IN BY KARON.

91
00:05:09,213 --> 00:05:10,446
-SISTER'S NOT LOVEY-DOVEY, ZURA?

92
00:05:10,446 --> 00:05:11,479
-HUH?

93
00:05:11,479 --> 00:05:14,346
-THEN IS RAETSEL
LOVEY-DOVEY WITH KA--

94
00:05:14,346 --> 00:05:15,879
-[ CHUCKLES ] NOW, NOW, UZURUA.

95
00:05:15,879 --> 00:05:17,746
-HOW FLATTERING.
WE LOOK THAT WAY?

96
00:05:17,746 --> 00:05:19,279
THAT CERTAINLY WOULD BE NICE.

97
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:21,879
-YOU SHOULDN'T TEASE ADULTS
LIKE THAT, YOU KNOW.

98
00:05:21,879 --> 00:05:23,546
-YOU ALWAYS TREAT ME AS A CHILD.

99
00:05:23,546 --> 00:05:24,913
YOU KNOW, I'M AT AN AGE

100
00:05:24,913 --> 00:05:27,279
WHERE MARRYING SOMEONE
WOULDN'T BE ODD.

101
00:05:27,279 --> 00:05:28,446
-[ LAUGHS ]

102
00:05:28,446 --> 00:05:31,779
WELL, AT MY AGE, ALL YOU
YOUNGSTERS LOOK THE SAME.

103
00:05:31,779 --> 00:05:34,079
I STILL SEE YOU AS FAKIR
AND MYTHO'S PLAYMATE.

104
00:05:34,079 --> 00:05:36,213
-THAT'S RIGHT. WHERE'S MYTHO?

105
00:05:36,213 --> 00:05:40,246
-OH, YEAH. HE'S AT SCHOOL NOW.
HIS DANCING CONSUMES HIM.

106
00:05:40,246 --> 00:05:41,613
-WEREN'T YOU ALWAYS WITH HIM,

107
00:05:41,613 --> 00:05:43,279
SAYING,
"I'LL PROTECT YOU MYTHO"?

108
00:05:43,279 --> 00:05:45,279
-AND I WILL.

109
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:47,379
YOU'RE STAYING HERE, RIGHT?

110
00:05:47,379 --> 00:05:50,279
-ACTUALLY, I PLAN TO STAY
AT THE WATER MILL.

111
00:05:50,279 --> 00:05:51,946
-I'LL WALK YOU THERE, THEN.

112
00:05:51,946 --> 00:05:53,279
-THANK YOU, BUT...

113
00:05:53,279 --> 00:05:56,279
I THINK I WANT TO TAKE
A LITTLE WALK WITH MISS DUCK.

114
00:05:56,279 --> 00:05:57,346
-HUH?

115
00:05:57,346 --> 00:05:59,779
-[ LAUGHS ]
I'M A TINY BIT JEALOUS.

116
00:05:59,779 --> 00:06:02,113
FAKIR WITH A GIRL
AS CUTE AS YOU.

117
00:06:02,113 --> 00:06:03,979
-OH, NO. I'M NOT CUTE AT ALL.

118
00:06:03,979 --> 00:06:06,679
THE TRUTH IS,
I'M ALWAYS FIGHTING WITH FAKIR.

119
00:06:06,679 --> 00:06:09,613
ACTUALLY, SOMETIMES I JUST CAN'T
STAND HIM, AND, YOU KNOW --

120
00:06:09,613 --> 00:06:11,046
-[ CHUCKLES ]

121
00:06:11,046 --> 00:06:15,413
I WONDER IF IT'S THANKS TO YOU
THAT FAKIR CHANGED SO MUCH.

122
00:06:15,413 --> 00:06:16,479
-HUH?

123
00:06:16,479 --> 00:06:19,779
-SAY, IS FAKIR
STILL WRITING STORIES?

124
00:06:19,779 --> 00:06:21,779
-WRITING STORIES?

125
00:06:21,779 --> 00:06:25,679
-THE STORIES THAT BOY
USED TO WRITE NOW AND AGAIN.

126
00:06:25,679 --> 00:06:27,679
SOMETIMES THEY CAME TRUE.

127
00:06:27,679 --> 00:06:29,146
-WHAT?

128
00:06:29,146 --> 00:06:31,646
THE STORIES HE WROTE
ACTUALLY CAME TRUE?

129
00:06:31,646 --> 00:06:36,913
-HE LOVED TO WRITE STORIES
FROM THE TIME HE WAS VERY SMALL.

130
00:06:36,913 --> 00:06:40,379
THEY WERE
JUST SILLY LITTLE STORIES.

131
00:06:40,379 --> 00:06:44,413
BUT SOMETIMES
PART OF THEM WOULD COME TRUE.

132
00:06:44,413 --> 00:06:47,046
HOWEVER,
AFTER HE CAME TO KARON'S HOUSE,

133
00:06:47,046 --> 00:06:49,413
HE JUST STOPPED WRITING
ALTOGETHER.

134
00:06:49,413 --> 00:06:52,646
-MISS RAETSEL?

135
00:06:52,646 --> 00:06:54,279
-I'VE SAID A LITTLE TOO MUCH.

136
00:06:54,279 --> 00:06:56,879
I WONDER IF FAKIR WILL SCOLD ME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

137
00:06:56,879 --> 00:07:01,846
-TO THINK FAKIR WROTE STORIES
AND THEY CAME TRUE!

138
00:07:01,846 --> 00:07:05,146
IF HE CAN DO THAT...

139
00:07:05,146 --> 00:07:09,579
MAYBE...

140
00:07:09,579 --> 00:07:11,446
-MISS DUCK?
-OH, SORRY!

141
00:07:11,446 --> 00:07:13,346
I JUST REMEMBERED SOMETHING!

142
00:07:13,346 --> 00:07:16,879
UM, IT WAS FUN TALKING TO YOU!

143
00:07:16,879 --> 00:07:18,313
-FAKIR HAS CHANGED.

144
00:07:18,313 --> 00:07:19,446
NO.

145
00:07:19,446 --> 00:07:24,979
THE ONE
WHO'S CHANGED THE MOST...IS ME.

146
00:07:24,979 --> 00:07:27,679
-PROTECT, HUH?

147
00:07:27,679 --> 00:07:31,213
HOW DO I PROTECT HIM?
WHO DO I FIGHT?

148
00:07:31,213 --> 00:07:33,746
-YOU HAVE TO HELP ME, FAKIR.

149
00:07:33,746 --> 00:07:36,113
MY HEART -- IT FEELS SO...

150
00:07:36,113 --> 00:07:39,679
-THE STORY
NO LONGER HAS NEED OF YOU.

151
00:07:39,679 --> 00:07:41,713
-THE FIGHT HAS BEGUN.

152
00:07:41,713 --> 00:07:43,646
THE STORY IS MOVING.

153
00:07:43,646 --> 00:07:46,546
WHETHER I'M HERE OR NOT.

154
00:07:46,546 --> 00:07:50,313
BUT ALL I HAVE IS A SWORD.

155
00:07:53,779 --> 00:07:55,746
[ CLANGING ]

156
00:07:55,746 --> 00:07:58,446
-I'LL PROTECT MYTHO
WITH THIS SWORD.

157
00:07:58,446 --> 00:08:00,279
-[ GASPS ] THERE YOU ARE!

158
00:08:00,279 --> 00:08:01,813
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

159
00:08:01,813 --> 00:08:03,813
HEY, FAKIR!
GUESS WHAT RAETSEL TOLD ME!

160
00:08:03,813 --> 00:08:06,446
SHE SAID STORIES YOU WRITE
HAVE THE POWER TO COME TRUE!

161
00:08:06,446 --> 00:08:08,946
-SHE WHAT?

162
00:08:08,946 --> 00:08:10,679
-IF YOU REALLY HAVE THAT POWER

163
00:08:10,679 --> 00:08:13,979
AND YOU WRITE A STORY WHERE
MYTHO GETS SAVED IN THE END --

164
00:08:13,979 --> 00:08:15,379
FAKIR?

165
00:08:15,379 --> 00:08:16,846
-WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

166
00:08:16,846 --> 00:08:17,879
-HUH?

167
00:08:17,879 --> 00:08:19,979
I SAID I HEARD
SOME OF THE STORIES

168
00:08:19,979 --> 00:08:22,913
YOU WROTE WHEN YOU WERE LITTLE
CAME TRUE.

169
00:08:22,913 --> 00:08:24,346
SO --
-BE QUIET.

170
00:08:24,346 --> 00:08:26,346
-HUH? BUT MYTHO COULD --

171
00:08:26,346 --> 00:08:27,346
-SHUT UP!

172
00:08:27,346 --> 00:08:28,613
-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

173
00:08:28,613 --> 00:08:31,079
WHY ARE YOU TALKING TO ME
THAT WAY?

174
00:08:31,079 --> 00:08:32,246
HEY!

175
00:08:32,246 --> 00:08:34,646
IF I REALLY COULD HELP MYTHO
BY MYSELF, FAKIR,

176
00:08:34,646 --> 00:08:36,313
I WOULDN'T BE ASKING YOU.

177
00:08:36,313 --> 00:08:38,813
BUT RIGHT NOW
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

178
00:08:38,813 --> 00:08:40,113
-I SAID BE QUIET!

179
00:08:40,113 --> 00:08:42,446
I'LL PROTECT MYTHO AS A KNIGHT.
END OF STORY.

180
00:08:42,446 --> 00:08:44,946
I WON'T TAKE ORDERS FROM YOU!

181
00:08:44,946 --> 00:08:46,579
-BUT --

182
00:08:46,579 --> 00:08:48,713
FAKIR, WAIT! HEY! LISTEN TO ME!

183
00:08:48,713 --> 00:08:50,579
FAKIR! COME ON, FAKIR!

184
00:08:50,579 --> 00:08:54,213
IF YOU COULD HELP MYTHO,
THEN WHY WON'T YOU?

185
00:08:54,213 --> 00:08:55,846
-[ PANTING ]

186
00:08:56,879 --> 00:08:58,379
-WHAT'S WITH YOU TWO?

187
00:08:58,379 --> 00:08:59,746
-[ LAUGHS ]

188
00:08:59,746 --> 00:09:01,879
WE WERE WAITING SO WE'D BE READY
WHEN YOU CAME HOME CRYING.

189
00:09:01,879 --> 00:09:04,113
-SO, WHAT HAPPENED
WITH THE WONDERFUL FAKIR?

190
00:09:04,113 --> 00:09:05,579
-I DON'T CARE
WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM.

191
00:09:05,579 --> 00:09:06,646
-GOOD, GOOD.

192
00:09:06,646 --> 00:09:09,179
GET MAD AND CRY
AS MUCH AS YOU WANT.

193
00:09:09,179 --> 00:09:11,879
-AND I THOUGHT WE'D BE ABLE
TO HELP MYTHO SOON.

194
00:09:11,879 --> 00:09:13,546
WHY?

195
00:09:23,446 --> 00:09:25,313
-BUT I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
-HE'S KIND OF SCARY.

196
00:09:25,313 --> 00:09:27,346
-LATELY IT'S LIKE
HE'S A TOTALLY DIFFERENT PERSON.

197
00:09:27,346 --> 00:09:28,946
-I'M GETTING SHIVERS
DOWN MY SPINE!

198
00:09:28,946 --> 00:09:31,513
[ DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING ]

199
00:09:36,213 --> 00:09:37,946
[ MUSIC STOPS,
ALL SCREAM ]

200
00:09:37,946 --> 00:09:40,646
-RAETSEL.

201
00:09:40,646 --> 00:09:43,446
-MYTHO, I'M JEALOUS OF YOU.

202
00:09:43,446 --> 00:09:44,579
-OF ME?

203
00:09:44,579 --> 00:09:47,446
-IF I COULD LIVE UNCHANGING
LIKE YOU --

204
00:09:47,446 --> 00:09:49,079
-THAT'S NOT HOW IT IS.

205
00:09:49,079 --> 00:09:51,846
SEE, I'M DIFFERENT
THAN I WAS BEFORE.

206
00:09:51,846 --> 00:09:55,446
I'VE GOTTEN MY HEART BACK,
AND THAT MEANS...

207
00:09:55,446 --> 00:09:58,446
NOW I CAN EVEN
ACCEPT YOUR LOVE FOR ME.

208
00:09:58,446 --> 00:10:01,446
-[ CHUCKLES ]
NOW THAT'S SOME HAPPY NEWS.

209
00:10:01,446 --> 00:10:04,313
MAYBE I'LL CALL OFF
THE WEDDING, THEN.

210
00:10:05,846 --> 00:10:06,846
-WEDDING?!

211
00:10:06,846 --> 00:10:08,646
AAH! THAT'S MR. MYTHO,

212
00:10:08,646 --> 00:10:11,413
WHICH MEANS THE GIRL
IS MISS RUE!

213
00:10:11,413 --> 00:10:14,379
THE TWO OF THEM
ARE GETTING MARRIED?

214
00:10:14,379 --> 00:10:16,113
IS THAT RIGHT? GETTING MARRIED?

215
00:10:16,113 --> 00:10:18,913
STUDENTS OF MINE
GETTING MARRIED BEFORE MY EYES?

216
00:10:18,913 --> 00:10:22,613
THERE IS NO HAPPIER, MORE JOYFUL
THING FOR A TEACHER THAN THIS!

217
00:10:22,613 --> 00:10:23,846
-CONGRATULATIONS.

218
00:10:23,846 --> 00:10:24,979
-OH, THANK YOU.

219
00:10:24,979 --> 00:10:26,946
-YOU DON'T LOOK VERY HAPPY.

220
00:10:26,946 --> 00:10:28,979
COULD IT BE YOU'RE WAVERING?

221
00:10:28,979 --> 00:10:30,213
-OF COURSE NOT.

222
00:10:30,213 --> 00:10:32,046
I WAS ONLY JOKING BEFORE.

223
00:10:32,046 --> 00:10:35,679
HANS LOVES ME DEEPLY
FROM THE BOTTOM OF HIS HEART.

224
00:10:35,679 --> 00:10:38,713
WITH HIM, I'M SURE I CAN HAVE
A HAPPY LIFE.

225
00:10:38,713 --> 00:10:39,713
[ GASPS ]

226
00:10:39,713 --> 00:10:40,913
-COME, NOW.

227
00:10:40,913 --> 00:10:43,613
YOU CAN'T LIE
TO YOUR OWN FEELINGS, RAETSEL.

228
00:10:43,613 --> 00:10:47,746
YOU'VE GOT A PURE AND BEAUTIFUL
HEART, HAVEN'T YOU?

229
00:10:47,746 --> 00:10:50,979
-I'M GOING NOW, MYTHO.

230
00:10:50,979 --> 00:10:54,446
-I WILL HAVE YOU LOVE ME
AND ME ALONE!

231
00:10:54,446 --> 00:10:57,213
SACRIFICE YOUR LIFE AND LOVE ME!

232
00:10:58,913 --> 00:11:01,213
-IF I DO WHAT FATHER SAYS,

233
00:11:01,213 --> 00:11:04,413
SOME DAY
HE'LL BE MY PRINCE ALONE.

234
00:11:04,413 --> 00:11:06,379
RIGHT, FATHER?

235
00:11:06,379 --> 00:11:09,513
-THE FIGHT
BETWEEN THE PRINCE AND THE RAVEN

236
00:11:09,513 --> 00:11:13,213
IS BEING FOUGHT WITH FIERCER
AND FIERCER DESPERATION

237
00:11:13,213 --> 00:11:15,879
IN A PLACE
WHERE NO ONE CAN SEE IT.

238
00:11:15,879 --> 00:11:18,146
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

239
00:11:32,043 --> 00:11:34,310
-SHE'S TOTALLY TOYING WITH HIM!

240
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:35,377
-THAT'S RIGHT.

241
00:11:35,377 --> 00:11:37,777
A FAKIR PLAYED THOROUGHLY
BY AN ADULT WOMAN

242
00:11:37,777 --> 00:11:40,510
AND THEN JUST TOSSED AWAY
LIKE YESTERDAY'S NEWSPAPER.

243
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:41,710
HOW WONDERFUL!

244
00:11:41,710 --> 00:11:46,177
-FAKIR SAID
HE WOULD PROTECT MYTHO, SO WHY?

245
00:11:46,177 --> 00:11:49,410
-I'LL PROTECT MYTHO AS A KNIGHT,
END OF STORY.

246
00:11:49,410 --> 00:11:51,410
I WON'T TAKE ORDERS FROM YOU!

247
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:53,477
-AND IT WAS STARTING
TO LOOK LIKE

248
00:11:53,477 --> 00:11:55,610
WE'D BE ABLE
TO WORK TOGETHER, TOO.

249
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:57,377
I DON'T LIKE THIS.

250
00:11:57,377 --> 00:11:59,877
NO WAY
I'LL LET IT STAY LIKE THIS!

251
00:11:59,877 --> 00:12:01,943
-HEY, WAIT!
-WHERE ARE YOU GOING, DUCK?!

252
00:12:01,943 --> 00:12:03,510
-TIME FOR THE SECOND ROUND, HUH?

253
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:06,010
THAT DUCK REALLY DOES
LOVE BATTLES, DOESN'T SHE?!

254
00:12:06,943 --> 00:12:09,010
-I SEE. SO, FAKIR SAID THAT.

255
00:12:09,010 --> 00:12:10,843
-I WANT TO HELP SOMEONE.

256
00:12:10,843 --> 00:12:13,977
AND HE'S SOMEONE IMPORTANT
TO FAKIR, TOO,

257
00:12:13,977 --> 00:12:16,810
SO I THOUGHT
IF FAKIR WROTE A STORY,

258
00:12:16,810 --> 00:12:20,410
MAYBE WE COULD HELP THIS PERSON,
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE --

259
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:21,710
-I'M SORRY.

260
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:23,377
THIS IS BECAUSE I'VE SAID
SOMETHING I SHOULDN'T HAVE.

261
00:12:23,377 --> 00:12:24,377
-HUH?

262
00:12:24,377 --> 00:12:25,577
-MISS DUCK, PLEASE.

263
00:12:25,577 --> 00:12:27,877
WILL YOU PRETEND
THAT YOU NEVER HEARD

264
00:12:27,877 --> 00:12:29,277
WHAT I TOLD YOU BEFORE?

265
00:12:29,277 --> 00:12:32,143
-BUT SAVING THIS GUY
WILL MAKE FAKIR HAPPY, TOO!

266
00:12:32,143 --> 00:12:35,243
-IN EXCHANGE, FAKIR WILL END UP
HURT AS WELL, THOUGH.

267
00:12:35,243 --> 00:12:36,710
-WHAT?

268
00:12:36,710 --> 00:12:38,010
-A LONG TIME AGO,

269
00:12:38,010 --> 00:12:40,710
A LOT OF CROWS ONCE SHOWED UP
IN GOLD CROWN TOWN.

270
00:12:40,710 --> 00:12:42,077
-CROWS?

271
00:12:42,077 --> 00:12:45,943
-THE CROWS ATTACKED THE
TOWNSPEOPLE INDISCRIMINATELY.

272
00:12:45,943 --> 00:12:47,410
FAKIR WAS A CHILD,

273
00:12:47,410 --> 00:12:50,977
BUT HE MUST HAVE WANTED TO DO
SOMETHING TO HELP.

274
00:12:50,977 --> 00:12:55,510
HE WROTE A STORY WHERE HE BECAME
A HERO AND DEFEATED THE CROWS.

275
00:12:56,677 --> 00:12:59,710
AND THEN,
JUST LIKE FAKIR HAD WRITTEN,

276
00:12:59,710 --> 00:13:02,077
THE CROWS CAME AND ATTACKED HIM.

277
00:13:02,077 --> 00:13:05,810
BUT THE ENDING WAS DIFFERENT
THAN HIS STORY.

278
00:13:08,710 --> 00:13:12,143
AFTERWARDS, HE GOT
SO HE NEVER TALKED ABOUT IT,

279
00:13:12,143 --> 00:13:14,943
AS IF HE SEALED
THOSE MEMORIES AWAY.

280
00:13:14,943 --> 00:13:17,243
HE STOPPED WRITING STORIES, TOO.

281
00:13:21,310 --> 00:13:22,510
-I NEVER KNEW

282
00:13:22,510 --> 00:13:25,443
FAKIR HAD SOMETHING LIKE THAT
HAPPEN TO HIM.

283
00:13:25,443 --> 00:13:29,610
-IT MUST STILL CUT HIM DEEPLY,
AND YET I -- MISS DUCK, PLEASE.

284
00:13:29,610 --> 00:13:32,043
GIVE FAKIR SOME SPACE.

285
00:13:32,043 --> 00:13:35,677
WHAT IN THE WORLD AM I DOING?

286
00:13:35,677 --> 00:13:37,277
[ DOOR OPENS ]

287
00:13:37,277 --> 00:13:38,577
[ GASPS ]

288
00:13:38,577 --> 00:13:41,043
-I CAME TO GET YOU, RAETSEL.

289
00:13:41,043 --> 00:13:43,043
MY BEAUTIFUL BRIDE.

290
00:13:43,043 --> 00:13:44,043
[ DRUM BANGING ]

291
00:13:44,043 --> 00:13:45,743
-LOVEY-DOVEY!
LOVEY-DOVEY!

292
00:13:45,743 --> 00:13:46,743
LOVE -- HUH?

293
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:49,110
DUCK, WHAT'S WRONG, ZURA?

294
00:13:49,110 --> 00:13:53,243
-I'M THE WORST.
WHAT SHOULD I SAY TO FAKIR?

295
00:13:53,243 --> 00:13:56,277
-YOU WANT TO SAY SOMETHING
TO FAKIR, ZURA?

296
00:13:56,277 --> 00:13:59,477
WOW! LOTS OF CROWS, ZURA!

297
00:13:59,477 --> 00:14:00,977
-THE WATER MILL!

298
00:14:00,977 --> 00:14:03,443
COULD MYTHO
BE TRYING TO GET RAETSEL?

299
00:14:19,143 --> 00:14:24,043
-RAETSEL, I'LL GIVE YOU A LOVE
WITH NO WAVERING.

300
00:14:24,043 --> 00:14:27,143
YOU'LL LOVE ONLY ME, WON'T YOU?

301
00:14:27,143 --> 00:14:30,377
-YES. MYTHO.

302
00:14:30,377 --> 00:14:34,310
-[ CHUCKLES ] MY RAETSEL.

303
00:14:34,310 --> 00:14:37,877
COME HERE AND GIVE
YOUR BEAUTIFUL HEART TO ME!

304
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:41,343
-I AM MYTHO'S BRIDE.

305
00:14:42,643 --> 00:14:45,110
-WAIT.

306
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:47,710
-WHO ARE YOU?

307
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:50,110
-I AM KNOWN AS PRINCESS TUTU.

308
00:14:50,110 --> 00:14:53,443
PLEASE COME AND DANCE WITH ME.

309
00:14:53,443 --> 00:14:54,843
WON'T YOU, MISS RAETSEL?

310
00:14:54,843 --> 00:14:56,843
-PRINCESS TUTU?

311
00:14:56,843 --> 00:14:58,277
-IF YOU REALLY HAVE THAT POWER

312
00:14:58,277 --> 00:15:00,843
AND YOU WRITE A STORY WHERE
MYTHO GETS SAVED IN THE END --

313
00:15:00,843 --> 00:15:03,310
-WHAT IS THIS AWFUL FEELING?

314
00:15:03,310 --> 00:15:06,643
THE POWER
TO MAKE STORIES COME TRUE?

315
00:15:06,643 --> 00:15:08,577
A POWER LIKE THAT IN ME?

316
00:15:08,577 --> 00:15:09,943
-LOVEY-DOVEY! LOVEY-DOVEY!

317
00:15:09,943 --> 00:15:11,777
LOVEY-DOVEY!
-THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

318
00:15:11,777 --> 00:15:13,343
-LOVEY-DOVEY! FAKIR!
-HUH?

319
00:15:13,343 --> 00:15:16,843
-IS IT MYTHO THAT MISS RAETSEL
IS LOVEY-DOVEY WITH, ZURA?

320
00:15:16,843 --> 00:15:18,277
-[ GASPS ]

321
00:15:23,577 --> 00:15:25,477
-THAT'S A LOVELY WEDDING DRESS.

322
00:15:25,477 --> 00:15:28,710
YOU HAVE SOMEONE
YOU'RE ENGAGED TO, RIGHT?

323
00:15:28,710 --> 00:15:30,443
THEN WHY ARE YOU --

324
00:15:30,443 --> 00:15:32,043
-KARON KNOWS HOW I FEEL,

325
00:15:32,043 --> 00:15:34,577
BUT WHEN I SAW HIM,
HE SAID NOTHING.

326
00:15:34,577 --> 00:15:35,677
HE DID NOTHING.

327
00:15:35,677 --> 00:15:36,977
-OH.

328
00:15:36,977 --> 00:15:40,743
-HANS, HOWEVER, HE ASSURES ME
OF HIS LOVE FOR ME.

329
00:15:40,743 --> 00:15:43,877
HE LOOKS ONLY AT ME
AND HOLDS ME CLOSE,

330
00:15:43,877 --> 00:15:46,210
AND I LOVE HIM DEARLY, AS WELL.

331
00:15:46,210 --> 00:15:50,043
YET NO MATTER WHAT I DO,
I SEE KARON'S FACE IN MY MIND.

332
00:15:50,043 --> 00:15:52,877
-YOU'RE SUFFERING BECAUSE YOU'RE
WAVERING BETWEEN TWO LOVES.

333
00:15:52,877 --> 00:15:55,010
LOVE ONLY ME
AND YOUR WAVERING WILL VANISH.

334
00:15:55,010 --> 00:15:57,943
-YOU MUSTN'T GO THERE.
DOES WAVERING SCARE YOU?

335
00:15:57,943 --> 00:16:01,243
IT'S SOMETHING YOU FEEL
BECAUSE YOU TRULY LOVE PEOPLE.

336
00:16:01,243 --> 00:16:04,210
-WHAT SCARES ME
IS THAT I MAY STILL LOVE KARON.

337
00:16:04,210 --> 00:16:06,477
WHEN THAT THOUGHT
CROSSES MY MIND,

338
00:16:06,477 --> 00:16:08,743
BEING WITH HIM IS --
IT'S PAINFUL.

339
00:16:08,743 --> 00:16:10,810
-KARON?

340
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:13,777
-I DON'T WANT TO WAVER!

341
00:16:15,743 --> 00:16:16,810
-RAETSEL.

342
00:16:16,810 --> 00:16:19,910
-THAT'S RIGHT.
IF YOU LOVE ONLY ME.

343
00:16:19,910 --> 00:16:22,210
-IF I BUT LOVE ONLY MYTHO.

344
00:16:22,210 --> 00:16:25,010
-NO! YOU'RE MAKING
A GRAVE MISTAKE, MISS RAETSEL!

345
00:16:25,010 --> 00:16:27,643
-JUST FORGET EVERYTHING ELSE
AND LOVE ONLY ME!

346
00:16:27,643 --> 00:16:30,977
-BOTH OF THESE THINGS REFLECT
YOUR TRUE HEART, MISS RAETSEL,

347
00:16:30,977 --> 00:16:34,343
BUT IS WHAT YOU ARE GRASPING AT
RIGHT NOW YOUR TRUE FEELINGS?

348
00:16:34,343 --> 00:16:36,843
-TRUE AND FALSE
HAVE NOTHING TO DO WITH IT.

349
00:16:36,843 --> 00:16:39,843
PEOPLE JUST LOVE OTHERS
BECAUSE THEY WANT TO BE LOVED.

350
00:16:39,843 --> 00:16:43,110
SHE WAVERS BECAUSE SHE WONDERS
WHICH ONE WILL LOVE HER MORE!

351
00:16:43,110 --> 00:16:45,677
-THAT PAIN IS HOW
YOU TRULY FEEL, SO WAKE UP!

352
00:16:45,677 --> 00:16:46,843
YOU WANT TO BE HAPPY

353
00:16:46,843 --> 00:16:49,110
WITH THE ONE YOU LOVE MOST,
DON'T YOU?

354
00:16:56,066 --> 00:16:59,300
-I KEPT ON WEIGHING THEIR LOVES
AGAINST EACH OTHER

355
00:16:59,300 --> 00:17:01,600
FOR THE SAKE
OF MY OWN HAPPINESS.

356
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:04,333
TO ESCAPE THE ACHING PAIN
OF MY WAVERING,

357
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:07,500
I SET OUT TO GET FAKIR
TO WRITE A STORY ABOUT ME.

358
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:10,000
EVEN THOUGH
I KNEW IT WOULD HURT HIM.

359
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,533
I'M A HORRIBLE WOMAN.

360
00:17:11,533 --> 00:17:14,233
-TO WANT TO BE LOVED
BY THOSE WE LOVE

361
00:17:14,233 --> 00:17:15,900
IS NOT AN EVIL FEELING.

362
00:17:15,900 --> 00:17:19,066
I'M SURE IT HURTS
TO WAVER BETWEEN TWO LOVES,

363
00:17:19,066 --> 00:17:23,100
BUT SIMPLY RUNNING AWAY WON'T
HELP YOU TO ESCAPE THAT PAIN.

364
00:17:27,066 --> 00:17:30,533
-NO, YOU --
YOU SHOULD BE LOVING ONLY ME!

365
00:17:30,533 --> 00:17:31,766
RAETSEL!

366
00:17:31,766 --> 00:17:35,500
-MYTHO, I WILL NOT ALLOW YOU
TO HARM RAETSEL.

367
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,233
-[ CHUCKLES ]

368
00:17:37,233 --> 00:17:39,233
HOW INTERESTING.

369
00:17:39,233 --> 00:17:41,400
[ WHOOSHING ]

370
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:50,700
[ CHUCKLES ]

371
00:17:50,700 --> 00:17:51,933
-STOP!

372
00:17:51,933 --> 00:17:53,066
THE TWO OF YOU FIGHTING,

373
00:17:53,066 --> 00:17:54,633
IT'S NOT GOING TO --
[ GASPS ]

374
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:08,333
-MYTHO, DO YOU FEEL NOTHING?
YOU WOULD EVEN USE RAETSEL?

375
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:13,433
-[ LAUGHS ]
I WAS MERELY TRYING TO SAVE HER!

376
00:18:16,166 --> 00:18:17,633
-FAKIR!

377
00:18:17,633 --> 00:18:19,266
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

378
00:18:22,933 --> 00:18:24,333
-TRYING TO SAVE HER?

379
00:18:24,333 --> 00:18:25,933
DON'T SUGARCOAT THINGS.

380
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:28,300
-WHAT? LIKE YOU'VE DONE
WITH YOUR SERVICE?

381
00:18:28,300 --> 00:18:31,133
KNIGHTS WHO CAN'T EVEN DIE
SHOULDN'T POINT FINGERS.

382
00:18:35,333 --> 00:18:37,566
PATHETIC.

383
00:18:37,566 --> 00:18:39,800
HOW LONG WILL YOU GO ON
SHAMING YOURSELF?

384
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,800
WIELDING THAT PLAY SWORD
OF YOURS.

385
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:44,033
-MYTHO, STOP IT!

386
00:18:44,033 --> 00:18:45,233
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

387
00:18:45,233 --> 00:18:47,466
YOU KNOW YOU CAN'T
LAY A FINGER ON ME, FAKIR.

388
00:18:47,466 --> 00:18:50,033
-THIS SWORD ISN'T
FOR SLAYING YOU WITH, MYTHO.

389
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:53,900
NOW, WAKE UP!
REMEMBER YOUR TRUE SELF, MYTHO!

390
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:55,266
-[ GASPS ]

391
00:18:55,266 --> 00:18:56,666
-MYTHO!

392
00:18:58,566 --> 00:19:00,700
-STOP IT.

393
00:19:02,566 --> 00:19:04,600
SHUT UP.

394
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,600
SHUT UP.

395
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:07,700
SHUT UP!

396
00:19:10,733 --> 00:19:13,400
AAH!

397
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,866
-FAKIR!

398
00:19:15,966 --> 00:19:17,600
-HUH?

399
00:19:20,866 --> 00:19:23,266
-STOP IT. DON'T HURT FAKIR.

400
00:19:23,266 --> 00:19:25,866
YOU HEAR ME, RAVEN? STOP THIS.

401
00:19:25,866 --> 00:19:27,066
-MYTHO?

402
00:19:27,066 --> 00:19:28,066
-RUN.

403
00:19:28,066 --> 00:19:31,366
DON'T -- DON'T COME NEAR ME.

404
00:19:31,366 --> 00:19:33,566
[ GROANS ]

405
00:19:36,033 --> 00:19:38,266
-MYTHO.

406
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:41,800
-RAETSEL. RAETSEL.

407
00:19:41,800 --> 00:19:43,833
-FAKIR, I -- I'M SORRY.

408
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:45,533
PLEASE FORGIVE ME.

409
00:19:45,533 --> 00:19:49,033
I WAS THINKING ONLY OF MYSELF.

410
00:19:49,033 --> 00:19:52,033
ALL I WANTED
WAS TO ESCAPE MY PAIN.

411
00:19:52,033 --> 00:19:54,533
AND I DID SOMETHING TO HURT YOU.

412
00:19:54,533 --> 00:19:56,766
I'M SORRY.

413
00:19:56,766 --> 00:19:57,800
-IT'S ALL RIGHT.

414
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:00,000
I'VE ALREADY FORGIVEN YOU,
RAETSEL.

415
00:20:02,800 --> 00:20:07,166
-EVEN THOUGH MISS RAETSEL
WAS SUFFERING SO MUCH,

416
00:20:07,166 --> 00:20:09,533
SHE TOLD ME -- SHE TOLD ME

417
00:20:09,533 --> 00:20:11,766
THAT I OUGHT TO GIVE YOU
SOME SPACE,

418
00:20:11,766 --> 00:20:13,566
AND THAT'S THE TRUTH.

419
00:20:13,566 --> 00:20:17,833
IT WASN'T IN MISS RAETSEL'S
HEART TO HURT YOU, FAKIR.

420
00:20:17,833 --> 00:20:19,133
FAKIR?

421
00:20:19,133 --> 00:20:22,133
-PLEASE TAKE CARE OF RAETSEL.

422
00:20:22,133 --> 00:20:24,366
-FAKIR.

423
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:30,333
IT WASN'T IN MISS RAETSEL'S
HEART TO HURT YOU.

424
00:20:32,733 --> 00:20:36,533
-DON'T HURT FAKIR.
YOU HEAR ME, RAVEN?

425
00:20:36,533 --> 00:20:37,766
STOP THIS!

426
00:20:37,766 --> 00:20:40,700
-IF I REALLY COULD HELP MYTHO
BY MYSELF, FAKIR,

427
00:20:40,700 --> 00:20:42,266
I WOULDN'T BE ASKING YOU.

428
00:20:42,266 --> 00:20:44,533
BUT RIGHT NOW
I CAN'T DO ANYTHING.

429
00:20:46,500 --> 00:20:48,100
-WHAT CAN I DO?

430
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,433
THAT'S RIGHT.

431
00:20:59,600 --> 00:21:02,800
I CAN WRITE A LETTER
TO THE PRESIDENT.

432
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:09,266
-FAKIR? BUT, WAIT, YOU'RE --

433
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:13,300
-RAETSEL.

434
00:21:13,300 --> 00:21:15,266
-RAETSEL!

435
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,066
-OH, GOOD MORNING.

436
00:21:18,066 --> 00:21:19,833
WHAT'S THAT IN YOUR HAND?

437
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,833
DID YOU WRITE A STORY FOR ME?

438
00:21:21,833 --> 00:21:23,400
KARON, I WANTED TO TELL YOU.

439
00:21:23,400 --> 00:21:25,433
HANS AND I
ARE GOING TO GET MARRIED.

440
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:26,433
-HUH?

441
00:21:26,433 --> 00:21:28,433
-SO I SEE. CONGRATULATIONS.

442
00:21:28,433 --> 00:21:29,466
-RAETSEL.

443
00:21:29,466 --> 00:21:31,966
-YOU SEE, I REALIZED
WHAT I WANTED

444
00:21:31,966 --> 00:21:34,833
WAS TO SAY A PROPER GOODBYE
TO KARON.

445
00:21:34,833 --> 00:21:37,066
BUT I'LL TAKE THIS.

446
00:21:37,066 --> 00:21:40,100
THANKS SO MUCH.

447
00:21:40,100 --> 00:21:43,466
-YOUR STORY
DIDN'T COME TRUE, HUH?

448
00:21:43,466 --> 00:21:45,033
-NO, IT DIDN'T.

449
00:21:45,033 --> 00:21:46,200
-HMM.

450
00:21:46,200 --> 00:21:48,366
-I THINK I WILL TRY WRITING ONE.

451
00:21:48,366 --> 00:21:49,366
-WHAT?

452
00:21:49,366 --> 00:21:52,433
-YOU KNOW, A STORY ABOUT MYTHO.

453
00:21:52,433 --> 00:21:53,666
-THAT'S DANGEROUS.

454
00:21:53,666 --> 00:21:56,266
THAT POWER IS TRULY DANGEROUS,
YOU KNOW?

455
00:21:56,266 --> 00:21:57,633
CAN SOMEONE LIKE YOU,

456
00:21:57,633 --> 00:22:00,033
WHO COULDN'T ATTAIN
MERE KNIGHTHOOD,

457
00:22:00,033 --> 00:22:02,333
REALLY MASTER
SUCH A POTENT CRAFT?

458
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:04,800
[ LAUGHS EVILLY ]

459
00:22:04,800 --> 00:22:08,066
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

460
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,933
-[ SINGING IN JAPANESE ]

461
00:22:49,900 --> 00:22:51,933
[ SINGING IN JAPANESE
CONTINUES ]

462
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:38,866
-THEY TOOK OUT THE ENDINGS
TO STOP THEM FROM BECOMING REAL?

463
00:23:38,866 --> 00:23:41,766
-HE'S AWAKENED.
THIS IS DANGEROUS!

